<font color="#FF0000">MAYA LIN--THANK YOU</font><br>
<tt>Sat Nov 30 12:36:40 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
To the self-effacing Maya:<br><br>
Before watching this excellent documentary, I only knew the bare outlines of the story of the maelstrom you found yourself in the middle of when you won the competition.  I was so impressed with the way you defended your &quot;strong clear vision&quot; (in the face of some rather vicious assaults)and how you continue to dedicate yourself to making lasting, meaningful and celebratory monuments and other works of art.  I felt like I was watching the story of a young Frank Lloyd Wright-- only without all the idiosyncracies.  I can easily see people wanting to take tours of all the Maya Lin memorials/houses/designs around the country/world someday--if it hasn't started already.  (Is there a list?)<br>
I know you didn't ask to become the architectural &quot;auteur&quot; of the Vietnam War and the Civil Rights Movement, but I can't imagine a better one.  I guess this is a fan letter.<br>
Best wishes in all your pursuits.<br><br>

<p><code>-- JSL26@aol.com  (Jeff Lubbers) </code><p>


